  <name>OpenUTAU</name>
  <summary>Open source singing synthesis platform</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      OpenUTAU is an open source UTAU successor that provides a modern approach to vocal synthesis.
      It serves as a comprehensive platform for creating synthetic singing voices using voicebanks
      and supports multiple synthesis techniques.
    </p>
    <p>
      Key features include:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Cross-platform compatibility with Windows, macOS, and Linux</li>
      <li>Support for multiple voicebank formats</li>
      <li>Advanced phoneme editing and timing control</li>
      <li>Plugin system for extensibility</li>
      <li>Modern user interface with dark theme support</li>
      <li>Real-time preview and playback</li>
      <li>MIDI import and export capabilities</li>
      <li>Extensive format support including UST, USTX, and VSQX files</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Whether you're a music producer, vocal synthesizer enthusiast, or someone interested in
      creating synthetic vocals, OpenUTAU provides the tools needed for professional-quality
      vocal synthesis work.
    </p>
  </description>

